{"lemma":"بُرْدُ","slug":"بُرْدُ","root":"ب.ر.د","root_slug":"ب-ر-د","root_link":"/words/roots/ب-ر-د","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"بُرْدُ","root":"برد","pos":"N","occurrence_count":2},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":8,"pos_tags":["adj","noun","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":19},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n2212","","n2217","n2218","n2219","n2220"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%A8%D9%8F%D8%B1%D9%92%D8%AF%D9%8F"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be or become cold, to cool off"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to feel cold"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to cool, chill"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to soothe, to alleviate (pain)"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to become fixed, settled, established","tags":["obsolete"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be or become cold"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to cool, to refrigerate","examples":[{"text":"بَرِّدْ حَشَايَ إِنِ ٱسْتَطَعْتَ بِلَفْظَةٍ / فَلَقَدْ تَضُرُّ إِذَا تَشَاءُ وَتَنْفَعُ"}]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to soothe, to alleviate"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to make obligatory, to establish","tags":["obsolete"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of بَرَدَ (barada) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"cold, coldness"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"cooling"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"cold (illness)"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"hail, hailstones","tags":["collective"]},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"cold"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"hailing"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to file, to pare"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"a kind of striped upper garment"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"a kind of coat","examples":[{"text":"خَرَجَ رَسُولِ اللَّهِ صَلَّى اللّٰهُ عَلَيْهِ وَسَلَّمَ وَعَلَيْهِ حُلَّةٌ حَمْرَاءُ، بُرُودٌ يَمَانِيَّةٌ، قِطْرِيٌّ.","english":"The prophet came out clad in red attire, burūd of Yemen, striped."}]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Compare Aramaic בַּרְדָא (barəḏā), Hebrew בָּרָד (bārāḏ), Amharic በረዶ (bärädo).\n\nBorrowed from Old Armenian բուրդ (burd)."},"ipa":["/ba.ra.da/","/ba.ru.da/","/bar.ra.da/","/bard/","/ba.rad/","/ba.rid/","/burd/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n2212","headword_ar":"بَرُدَ","root":"brd","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"buruwdapN","text_ar":"بُرُودَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, M, Mgh, Msb, K;) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"barada","text_ar":"بَرَدَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, Msb, K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"barodN","text_ar":"بَرْدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (M, Msb;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a thing, S, Msb, and the latter said of water, Msb)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, cold, chill,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"cool;"},{"kind":"text","text":"[see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"barodN","text_ar":"بَرْدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"below;] (S, M;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"its heat became allayed."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb.) The latter verb is also used transitively, as will be shown below. (Msb.) ―         -b2-  [Hence,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baruda maDojaEahu","text_ar":"بَرُدَ مَضْجَعَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[lit."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"His bed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"place of sleep, became cold;"},{"kind":"text","text":"meaning] (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he went on a journey."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"barada","text_ar":"بَرَدَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"also signifies (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He died;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(As, T, S, A, K;) because death is the non-existence of the heat of the soul; (L;) or it is allusive to the extinction of the natural heat; or to the cessation of motion. (MF.) For ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"barada","text_ar":"بَرَدَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (MF,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (Mgh,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"barodN","text_ar":"بَرْدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (MF,) likewise signifies (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, still, quiet,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"motionless;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh, MF;) for instance, a slaughtered sheep or goat [&c.]. (Mgh.) And (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It"},{"kind":"text","text":"(beverage of the kind called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nabiy*","text_ar":"نَبِيذ"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became still, and without briskness."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA, from a trad.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ruEiba fabarada makaAnahu","text_ar":"رُعِبَ فَبَرَدَ مَكَانَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He became frightened, and remained motionless in his place;"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"makaAnahu","text_ar":"مَكَانَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"meaning"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiY makaAnahu","text_ar":"فِى مَكَانَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": and hence,] (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he became amazed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"stupified."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baradato Eayonuhu","text_ar":"بَرَدَتْ عَيْنُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The pain in his eye became allayed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"stilled."},{"kind":"text","text":"(L.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"barada A^amorunaA","text_ar":"بَرَدَ اَمْرُنَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Our affair,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"case, became easy."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA, from a trad. [See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baAridN","text_ar":"بَارِدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".]) ―         -b5-  Also, inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"barod","text_ar":"بَرْد"},{"kind":"text","text":", [which see below,] (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He slept."},{"kind":"text","text":"(T.) ―         -b6-  And hence, (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It remained,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became permanent,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fixed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"settled."},{"kind":"text","text":"(T.) So in the saying,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lamo yaborudo biyadiY minohu $ayo'N","text_ar":"لَمْ يَبْرُدْ بِيَدِى مِنْهُ شَيْءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"There did not remain,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"become permanent"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fixed"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"settled, in my hand, thereof, anything."},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, L. *) You say also,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"barada A^asiyrFA fiY A^ayodiyohimo","text_ar":"بَرَدَ اَسِيرًا فِى اَيْدِيْهِمْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He remained safely a captive in their hands."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"barada","text_ar":"بَرَدَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiY A^ayodiyhmo salomFA","text_ar":"فِى اَيْدِيهمْ سَلْمًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He became a permanent captive, remaining in their hands, not to be ransomed nor liberated nor demanded."},{"kind":"text","text":"(L.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"barada Almawoti","text_ar":"بَرَدَ المَوْتِ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EalaYmuSoTalaAhu","text_ar":"عَلَىمُصْطَلَاهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Death fixed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"settled,"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"upon his face and extremities,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"upon his limbs,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"upon his arms and legs and face and every prominent part,"},{"kind":"text","text":"which become cold at the time of death, and which are warmed at the fire. (AHeyth, L.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"barada Almawoti Ealayohi","text_ar":"بَرَدَ المَوْتِ عَلَيْهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Death became impressed upon him;"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the marks,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"signs, of death became apparent upon him."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A.) ―         -b7-  [And hence, app.,] (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a right, or due,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became incumbent,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"obligatory,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and established."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"barada liY Haq~iY EalaY fulaAnK","text_ar":"بَرَدَ لِى حَقِّى عَلَى فُلَانٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"My right,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"due, became incumbent,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"obligatory, on such a one, and established against him."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, * A, * TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA barada laka EalaY fulaAnK","text_ar":"مَا بَرَدَ لَكَ عَلَى فُلَانٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"What hath become incumbent,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"obligatory, to thee, on such a one, and established against him?"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"what hath become owed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"due, to thee, by,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from, such a one?"},{"kind":"text","text":"as also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA *aAba laka Ealayohi","text_ar":"مَا ذَابَ لَكَ عَلَيْهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"barada liY Ealayohi","text_ar":"بَرَدَ لِى عَلَيْهِ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ka*aA mina AlmaAli","text_ar":"كَذَا مِنَ المَالِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such an amount of the property,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of property, became incumbent,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"obligatory, to me, on him, and established against him;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became owed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"due, to me, by,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from, him."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S.) ―         -b8-  Also, (K,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"barodN","text_ar":"بَرْدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA, [but see the next sentence,]) (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a man)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, weak;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and so"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"burida","text_ar":"بُرِدَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", a verb like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EuniYa","text_ar":"عُنِىَ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (K.) And, inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"buraAdN","text_ar":"بُرَادٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"buruwdN","text_ar":"بُرُودٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, K,) (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, languid,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"weak and languid, from leanness"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"disease:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"weak in the legs, from hunger"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fatigue."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Ibn-Buzurj, T.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"barada mux~uhu","text_ar":"بَرَدَ مُخُّهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (A, K,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"barodN","text_ar":"بَرْدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,) (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, lean,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"emaciated;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, K;) and so"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baradato EiZaAmuhu","text_ar":"بَرَدَتْ عِظَامُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (A, TA.) ―         -b9-  (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a sword [or the like])"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, blunt."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K.)       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baradahu","text_ar":"بَرَدَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Msb, K,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"barodN","text_ar":"بَرْدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (K;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"br~dhu","text_ar":"برّدهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, M, Msb, K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taboriydN","text_ar":"تَبْرِيدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He made it,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"rendered it,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(for ex., water, M, Msb, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"cold, chill,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"cool:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, &c.:) but the latter has an intensive signification ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he made it,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"rendered it, very cold,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"very cool"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (Msb:) or both signify, (K,) or the former signifies, (M, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he mixed it with snow:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K:) one does not say ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Abrdhu","text_ar":"ابردهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", except in a bad dialect. (S.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bar~idiyhi","text_ar":"بَرِّدِيهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", being used by a poet for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"balo ridiyhi","text_ar":"بَلْ رِدِيهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", has been erroneously supposed to mean “Make thou it hot.” (M.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baradanaA All~ayolu","text_ar":"بَرَدَنَا اللَّيْلُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (aor. and inf. n. as above, M,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"barada EalayonaA","text_ar":"بَرَدَ عَلَيْنَا"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The night affected us with its cold."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saqayotuhu $arobapF baradato fuw^aAdahu","text_ar":"سَقَيْتُهُ شَرْبَةً بَرَدَتْ فُوَادَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, M, *) aor. and inf. n. as above, (S,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I gave him to drink a draught"},{"kind":"page_break","n":184},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that cooled his heart:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M:) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baradotu bihaA fuw^aAdahu","text_ar":"بَرَدْتُ بِهَا فُوَادَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with which I cooled his heart"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (So in the T.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fuw^aAdaka bi$arobapK","text_ar":"فُوَادَكَ بِشَرْبَةٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bar~ido","text_ar":"بَرِّدْ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Cool thy heart by a draught."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AisoqiniY sawiyqFA A^aborudo bihi kabidiY","text_ar":"اِسْقِنِى سَوِيقًا اَبْرُدْ بِهِ كَبِدِى"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Give thou me to drink"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"swyq","text_ar":"سويق"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with which I may cool my liver"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (T.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"barada Eayonuhu biAlokuHoli","text_ar":"بَرَدَ عَيْنُهُ بِالْكُحْلِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (A'Obeyd, T, M,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"biAlobaruwdi","text_ar":"بِالْبَرُودِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Msb, K,) aor. and inf. n. as above, (M,) ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He cooled his eye with the collyrium,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he applied the cooling collyrium to his eye,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, * S, M, * Msb, K, *)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and allayed its pain."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M.) The following words, cited by IAar,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"baraduwA gawaAriba A^ayonuqK Hudobi"},{"kind":"text","text":"[lit."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"They cooled the fore parts of the humps,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the backs, of humped she-camels"},{"kind":"text","text":"], mean (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"they put off from them their saddles, that their backs might become cool."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M.) You say also, ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bar~ido","text_ar":"بَرِّدْ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Zahora farasika saAEapF","text_ar":"ظَهْرَ فَرَسِكَ سَاعَةً"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Relieve thy horse from riding"},{"kind":"text","text":"[lit."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"cool his back"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"awhile."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A.) And ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laA tubar~ido","text_ar":"لَا تُبَرِّدْ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eano fulaAnK","text_ar":"عَنْ فُلَانٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Do not thou alleviate the punishment"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the world to come"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"due to the offence of such a one by thy reviling him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"cursing him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"when he has acted injuriously to thee. (T, S, * M, * A, * L.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"barada Alxuboza","text_ar":"بَرَدَ الخُبْزَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (T, L, K,)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"biAlomaA='i","text_ar":"بِالْمَا=ءِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (T,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He poured"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"cold"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"water upon the bread,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, L, K,) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"moistened it"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"therewith:"},{"kind":"text","text":"see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baruwdN","text_ar":"بَرُودٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (T, L.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"burida","text_ar":"بُرِدَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a verb like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EuniYa","text_ar":"عُنِىَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a company of men)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"was hailed upon."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, K.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"buridati","text_ar":"بُرِدَتِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA^aruDu","text_ar":"الاَرُضُ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The land,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ground, was hailed upon."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S.)       -A3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"barada","text_ar":"بَرَدَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, M, &c.,) aor"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"barodN","text_ar":"بَرْدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Mgh, TA,) also signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He filed"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, Mgh, K) iron, (S, M, &c.,) and the like, (M,) with a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"miborad","text_ar":"مِبْرَد"},{"kind":"text","text":".(S, M, Mgh, Msb, K.)       -A4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baradahu","text_ar":"بَرَدَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Abrdhu","text_ar":"ابردهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He sent him as a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bariyd","text_ar":"بَرِيد"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"messenger on a postmule"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"post-horse"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (K.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"barada barydFA","text_ar":"بَرَدَ بَريدًا"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Abrdhu","text_ar":"ابردهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (A,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He sent a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bryd","text_ar":"بريد"},{"kind":"text","text":". (M, A.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_iloyahi","text_ar":"اـِلْيَهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Abrd","text_ar":"ابرد","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alyh bariydFA","text_ar":"اليه بَرِيدًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Abrd","text_ar":"ابرد","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (T, TA.)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He sent to him a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bryd","text_ar":"بريد"},{"kind":"text","text":". (T, S.)"}],"source_refs":["M","Msb","K","MF","Mgh","TA","A","S","T","L"]},{"entry_id":"n2217","headword_ar":"بَرْدٌ","root":"brd","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"buruwdapN","text_ar":"بُرُودَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"[originally inf. ns.]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Cold; coldness; chill; chilness; cool,"},{"kind":"text","text":"as a subst.;"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"coolness;"},{"kind":"text","text":"the former,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"contr. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Har~N","text_ar":"حَرٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, M, A, Msb;) and the latter,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaraArapN","text_ar":"حَرَارَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S.) ―         -b2-  And [hence] the former, (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Pleasantness; enjoyment; ease; comfort:"},{"kind":"text","text":"as in the saying,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nasoA^aluka Aljan~apa wa barodahaA","text_ar":"نَسْاَلُكَ الجَنَّةَ وَ بَرْدَهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"We ask of Thee Paradise and its pleasantness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c. (L.) ―         -b3-  Also (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Sleep:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, S, M, A, K:) [an inf. n. used as a subst.:] so in the Kur lxxviii. 24: (S, M, K:) for sleep cools a man: (TA:) or, accord. to I'Ab, it there means the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"coldness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"coolness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"of beverage. (T.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"manaEa Albaradu Albaroda","text_ar":"مَنَعَ البَرَدُ البَرْدَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The hail prevented sleep."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A.) ―         -b4-  And (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Saliva:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Th, T, M, K:) so, accord. to Th, in the saying of El-'Arjee,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"wa A_ino $iy^oti lamo A^aToEamu nuqaAxFA wa laA barodaA"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And if thou desire, I will not taste sweet water, nor saliva"},{"kind":"text","text":"[from any lips but thine]. (T, M, * TA. [But this is cited in the S as an ex. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"barod","text_ar":"بَرْد"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifying"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sleep."},{"kind":"text","text":"]) ―         -b5-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baAridN","text_ar":"بَارِدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". ―         -b6-  [Hence,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlbarodaAni","text_ar":"البَرْدَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA^aboradaAni","text_ar":"الاَبْرَدَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aboradu","text_ar":"اَبْرَدُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":["T","S","M","A","K","TA","Th"]},{"entry_id":"n2218","headword_ar":"بُرْدٌ","root":"brd","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A kind of garment;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a kind of striped garment:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K:) accord. to some,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the description termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wa$oYN","text_ar":"وَشْىٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"variegated"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (M:) or particular kinds thereof are distinguished by such terms as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"burodu EaSobK","text_ar":"بُرْدُ عَصْبٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"burodu wa $oYK","text_ar":"بُرْدُ وَ شْىٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Msb:) also, (as a coll. gen. n., TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"garments of the kind called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^akosiyapN","text_ar":"اَكْسِيَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", [pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kisaA='N","text_ar":"كِسَا=ءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":",]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"which are wrapped round the body;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"one of which is called"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"burodapN","text_ar":"بُرْدَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (M, K:) or, as Lth says, the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"burod","text_ar":"بُرْد"},{"kind":"text","text":"is ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"well-known"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"garment"},{"kind":"text","text":"],"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the kind called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"buruwdu","text_ar":"بُرُودُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlEaSobi","text_ar":"العَصْبِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"buruwdu Alwa$oYi","text_ar":"بُرُودُ الوَشْىِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (T;) but the ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"burodapN","text_ar":"بُرْدَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a garment of the kind called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kisaA='N","text_ar":"كِسَا=ءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"four-sided, black, and somewhat small, worn by the Arabs of the desert:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, S, Mgh, * Msb, * TA:) or this latter (the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"brdp","text_ar":"بردة"},{"kind":"text","text":") is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a striped garment of the kind called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$amolapN","text_ar":"شَمْلَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (T:) or it is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an oblong piece of woollen cloth, fringed:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M:) Sh says, I saw an Arab of the desert wearing"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a piece of woollen cloth resembling a napkin, wrapped round the body like an apron;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and on my saying to him, What dost thou call it? he answered,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"burodap","text_ar":"بُرْدَة"},{"kind":"text","text":": (T:) [the modern"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"brdp","text_ar":"بردة"},{"kind":"text","text":", in every case in which I have seen it, I have observed to be"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an oblong piece of thick woollen cloth, generally brown or of a dark or ashy dust-colour, and either plain, or having stripes so narrow and near together as to appear, at a little distance, of one colour; used both to envelop the person by day and as a night-covering:"},{"kind":"text","text":"the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"brdp","text_ar":"بردة"},{"kind":"text","text":"of Mohammad is described as about seven feet and a half in length, and four and a half in width, and in colour either"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^axoDar","text_ar":"اَخْضَر"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aHomar","text_ar":"اَحْمَر"},{"kind":"text","text":", i. e. of a dark or ashy dust-colour or brown; for such are the significations of these two epithets when applied to a garment of this kind, and in some other cases:] the pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"burodN","text_ar":"بُرْدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aborudN","text_ar":"اَبْرُدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aboraAdN","text_ar":"اَبْرَادٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[both pls. of pauc.] and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"buruwdN","text_ar":"بُرُودٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"buradN","text_ar":"بُرَدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (IAar, T,) or this last is pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"burodapN","text_ar":"بُرْدَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, M,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"biraAdN","text_ar":"بِرَادٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", like as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qiraATN","text_ar":"قِرَاطٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"quroTN","text_ar":"قُرْطٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", or this, also, is pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"burodapN","text_ar":"بُرْدَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", like as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"biraAmN","text_ar":"بِرَامٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"buromapN","text_ar":"بُرْمَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (M.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*uwburodK","text_ar":"ذُوبُرْدٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":", as opposed to"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*uw kisaA='i","text_ar":"ذُو كِسَا=ءِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", means (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A rich man."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ej","text_ar":"عج"},{"kind":"text","text":".) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waqaEa bayonuhumaA qad~u buruwdK yumonapK","text_ar":"وَقَعَ بَيْنُهُمَا قَدُّ بُرُودٍ يُمْنَةٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (so in copies of the K, in the TA"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yumanapK","text_ar":"يُمَنَةٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":",) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"buruwdK","text_ar":"بُرُودٍ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vamiynapK","text_ar":"ثَمِينَةٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (so in a copy of the A,) (tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"There happened between them two the rending of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"buruwd","text_ar":"بُرُود"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the fabric of El-Yemen,"},{"kind":"text","text":"accord. to the reading in the K, or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of costly"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"buruwd","text_ar":"بُرُود"},{"kind":"text","text":", accord. to the reading in the A,] means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"they arrived at a great,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"severe, state of affairs;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K;) or is said of two men who have contended together in vehement altercation so that they have rent each other's garments; (A;) [accord. to the reading in the K,] because"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yumanN","text_ar":"يُمَنٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", [in the CK"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yumon","text_ar":"يُمْن"},{"kind":"text","text":",] which are"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"buruwd","text_ar":"بُرُود"},{"kind":"text","text":"of El-Yemen, are not rent save on account of some great, or severe, thing, or affair. (K.) ―         -b4-  ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"humaA fiY burodapi","text_ar":"هُمَا فِى بُرْدَةِ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^axomaAsK","text_ar":"اَخْمَاسٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"means (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"They two do one deed;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"act alike;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar, M, K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and resemble each other, as though they were in one"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"burodap","text_ar":"بُرْدَة"},{"kind":"text","text":": (IAar, M:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"they two have become near together, and in a state of agreement."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xms","text_ar":"خمس"},{"kind":"text","text":", q. v.) ―         -b5-  And ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"salaba AlS~ahobaA='a burodatahaA","text_ar":"سَلَبَ الصَّهْبَا=ءَ بُرْدَتَهَا","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it, deprived the wine of its colour."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A.) ―         -b6-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"burodaA AljaraAdi","text_ar":"بُرْدَا الجَرَادِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (T,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aljunodabi","text_ar":"الجُنْدَبِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S,) (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The two wings"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the locust,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the species called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jndb","text_ar":"جندب"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (T, S.) ―         -b7-  And ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"burodapu","text_ar":"بُرْدَةُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlD~aA^oni","text_ar":"الضَّاْنِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A certain sort of milk."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.)"}],"source_refs":["M","K","Msb","T","S","IAar"]},{"entry_id":"n2219","headword_ar":"بَرَدٌ","root":"brd","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Hail; what descends from the clouds, resembing pebbles;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, Msb;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"frozen rain;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lth, T;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"what is called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hab~u AlgamaAmi","text_ar":"حَبُّ الغَمَامِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, Msb, K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hab~u Almuzoni","text_ar":"حَبُّ المُزْنِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb) [i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the grains,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"berries, of the clouds:"},{"kind":"text","text":"a coll. gen. n., of which the n. un. is with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":", signifying"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a hailstone"},{"kind":"text","text":"]."}],"source_refs":["S","A","Msb","K"]},{"entry_id":"n2220","headword_ar":"بَرِدٌ","root":"brd","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Possessing coldness"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"coolness:"},{"kind":"text","text":"an epithet applied to the [plant called]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Sil~iyaAn","text_ar":"صِلِّيَان"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saHaAbN baridN","text_ar":"سَحَابٌ بَرِدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (T, S, M, K,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aboradu","text_ar":"اَبْرَدُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Clouds containing hail"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, S, M, K *)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and cold."},{"kind":"text","text":"(T.) You say also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saHaAbapN baridapN","text_ar":"سَحَابَةٌ بَرِدَةٌ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A cloud containing hail"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, S, M, A *)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and cold;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T;) but not"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sHAbp","text_ar":"سحابة"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"barodaA='u","text_ar":"بَرْدَا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (M.)"}],"source_refs":["T","S","M","K"]}]}}